name: Celine Dion
summary: Celine Dion has provided updates on her health struggles. She has disclosed that the burden of concealing her condition became overwhelming, which resulted in her using life-threatening doses of Valium to alleviate muscle spasms. Dion's illness has also caused spasms severe enough to fracture her ribs. Despite her challenges, Dion has announced her return to performing and has even discussed the possibility of singing at the Olympics. To prepare for potential emergencies, her 13-year-old twins have undergone "crisis" drills and are equipped with panic buttons. Dion has also given a poignant account of her condition, describing the spasms as "somebody strangling you."

name: Jerry West
summary: Legendary Los Angeles Lakers player and NBA logo inspiration Jerry West has passed away at 86. Known as "The Logo," West's silhouette adorns the NBA's iconic emblem. He holds a remarkable NBA Finals record, with no team ever recovering from a 3-1 deficit against his Lakers in the Finals. Current NBA star LeBron James and others have expressed their admiration for West, who inspired HBO's "Winning Time" character despite the portrayal being inaccurate. West's legacy includes his success with the Lakers and shaping the NBA into what it is today. Despite his passing, his iconic silhouette and contributions to the sport will continue to be remembered.
